When information about this affair first became public last year, Mr. Ensign apologized to his constituents and resigned his position in the Senate, where he had ranked fourth among Republicans.
Two weeks ago, after going unnoticed for many months, Mr. Ensign told reporters he was seeking a third term in the Senate.
In announcing that Mr. Ensign would no longer be the target of police investigations, his press secretary, Jennifer Cooper, said the senator hoped the ethics committee would quickly follow the Justice Department's example and drop its investigation.
"Senator Ensign looks forward to continuing his hard work of service to the people of Nevada," she said.
